comments: Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) forearm grazes Murray's (ATL) side during the put-back attempt in the paint, and the contact is marginal.
Joe (OKC) brings his hand to the ball and cleanly deflects it during the release of Johnson's (ATL) pass.
Johnson (ATL) aligns along Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive toward the basket.
Dort (OKC) comes alongside Young (ATL) at the end of the drive and marginal lower body contact occurs as he releases his pass.
The ball last touches Williams (OKC) before falling out of bounds. Possession is properly awarded to Atlanta.
Bey (ATL) firms up in Dort's (OKC) path and his arms come out slightly as he disengages from Dort during the screen.
Dort (OKC) moves into Young's (ATL) space and initiates body contact that affects Young's SQBR with the ball.
Williams' (OKC) hand slides off of the ball as he comes together with Capela (ATL) after the inbound pass, and the body contact is marginal.
Dort (OKC) is moving alongside Young's (ATL) path and marginal body contact occurs during Young's drive.
Murray's (ATL) shot attempt does not come into contact with the rim and the shot clock expires while it is in the air. Possession is properly awarded to Oklahoma City.
Joe (OKC) beats Young (ATL) to the spot on the floor and absorbs the marginal contact as the two players come together in the backcourt.
Williams (OKC) moves alongside Murray's (ATL) path and legally contests Murray's driving shot attempt in the paint.
Johnson (ATL) returns to the floor and comes together with Joe (OKC), and marginal contact occurs as both players lose their balance and fall to the floor.
Joe's (OKC) arm briefly comes around Johnson's (ATL) arm as they engage during the rebounding opportunity, and the contact is marginal.
Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) off-arm comes out slightly as he changes direction after his gather, and the contact with Bogdanovic (ATL) is marginal.
Bogdanovic (ATL) moves alongside Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) path and absorbs the marginal contact after his gather into the driving shot attempt.
Joe (OKC) jumps towards Johnson (ATL) and initiates illegal contact to his body.
Murray (ATL) and Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) come together during the inbound, and marginal contact occurs.
Forrest (ATL) legally contests Joe's (OKC) perimeter jump shot attempt.
